text: NIRRIN Analytics About Founded in the biotech hub of the world, NIRRIN Analytics employs disruptive technologies and methodologies to deliver , , , monitoring of aqueous solutions that can enable improved process control, faster process development, and adaptive manufacturing for the biopharma and life science NIRRIN Analytics leverages NIR technology, innovative chemometric analytical methods, and knowledge to deliver effective, robust, and solutions that are , flexible, and scalable to address dynamic customer Board of Directors Bryan Hassell, Bryan Hassell earned his in Applied Physics at Harvard University where his dissertation focused on development of novel in vitro disease His work resulted in the discovery of new molecular mechanisms behind therapeutic resistance in cell lung cancer patients and the resulting technology led to 2 patents and a He also earned his M.S. in Mechanical Engineering from Villanova University focusing on heat transfer and fluid dynamics, after which he joined the Department of Defense within NAVSEA Carderock Within the DoD he worked as an R&D scientist working on novel heat transfer solutions for radar and weapon systems, as well as a Principal Investigator Technical Point of Contact on several BAA solicitations and SBIR STTR programs under the Office of the Secretary of Defense, Office of Naval Research and Patrick Shaffer, Patrick Shaffer has a PhD in theoretical chemistry from UC Berkeley and has expertise in simulation modeling, spectroscopy, biophysics and machine He worked as a data scientist at Mirah and did his postdoctoral research in biomolecular simulation at ETH Zurich, where he developed algorithms that significantly extended the capabilities of these Jonathan Hartmann, MBA John Ho, David Michael, MBA David Seldin, MBA Our Team Careers We are looking for a Lab Technician II, who will be responsible for both experimental and or numerical programming Key experimental engineering activities include: - Culture and maintenance of suspension and cells - Maintaining live bioreactors while obtaining data - Engineering design of new probe interfaces Key numerical activities include: - Developing chemometric models using Matlab Python C++ - Developing graphical user interfaces (GUIs) to integrate data acquisition, analysis and presentation Qualifications: - Technical Bachelor’s or Master’s, with a focus on either - Bio Chemical Mechanical Engineering, Physics, Biology or - Computer Science strongly - year of work experience, with a preference for candidates with technical experience and - Experience with bio and biochemistry assays ELISA, mass , protein purification - Experience with CAD tools SolidWorks and printing rapid-prototyping - About Visit Join Open Navigation Login Commercial Banking Tech & Startup Banking Personal Banking Mortgage About Team Careers Contact Login Resources LinkedIn Twitter Facebook Instagram Debit Card from Nashville Bank on Table A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US You might be wondering… Am I a creator? A studio is a place where creators do their And we are the bank for Nashville’s Whether you’re designing a company or creating a better life for your family, crafting a song or writing code, orchestrating social change or enhancing the quality of care, we want to collaborate with We say welcome to the doers, , leaders… and even the brilliant What does it mean to empower creators? [Alright, this is about to get ] WE START FROM A PHILOSOPHICAL What makes human beings uniquely human is the capacity to create something from Our role as bankers is to empower creators with resources – whether that’s capital [‘cause it takes money to create things], education, advice, or simply safeguarding and managing your After all, those finances are fuel for and the result of Humans are also social Creating is more fun with others! We think a bank can serve as a unique nexus point for bringing together people from all walks of life and different industries – where they have a common connection [Studio Bank]. We want to build Hence, a [and very social] approach to In a community, we think humans ought to practice hospitality with one And we’re here to do just that [with modern technology]. In fact, we view ourselves as part of the hospitality industry, providing a member experience inspired by this high form of It’s a service mentality unlike any other bank in Nashville How did this get started? Studio started like most things in Nashville, with a group of friends and a dream: What if a bank could become a force for creativity, instead of an obstacle to it? With that question in mind, we began to rethink and reinvent the typical banking Fusing innovative technology with a zeal for genuine hospitality, we created a bank that is: uncommonly modern and surprisingly human We’re here to empower, protect, and inspire you in the things you From our office on Demonbreun and through our community of members, we are relentlessly committed to the future of Nashville and its many influences Our team of veteran bankers – many of whom are entrepreneurs and artists themselves — is committed to fueling the creative ethos of our Studio is a boutique bank founded and located in our hometown of Nashville, We provide organizations, families, and individuals with sophisticated financial Deposits and loans… and a few other membership Why the French Bulldog? From Nashville’s French roots to the social personality of the dog, our Frenchie is more than just a He’s the perfect mascot to represent our brand — smart, active, adaptable, and bred to be a companion French bulldogs are sophisticated but not A rare and one of a kind Our proudest moments? LiST Settlements is a Fintech startup for the secondary life insurance market (the reselling of insurance policies that the original policyholders can no long afford or no longer need) that provides value and access to both policyholders and LiST expands the secondary market by creating a new and efficient marketplace, offering investors of all sizes the opportunity to freely participate in this asset LiST enables investors to invest in a transparent and diversified format while simultaneously helping policyholders maximize the value of their WHO IS BEHIND LiST? LiST was started by and is managed by three entrepreneurs with over a of combined experience in finance and In previous ventures, they used their deep knowledge of technological tools to create complex financial models for leading players in financial Their special talent is in forming and fostering partnerships by paying attention to the needs of all the They founded LiST because they saw an opportunity to provide a valuable service to both investors and policyholders and knew how to create an innovative process to bring them WHY INVEST IN LIFE SETTLEMENTS? Life Settlements are considered to be pure alpha assets due to their historically low correlation to the stock market—these investments are generally not affected by the forces that control the stock Life settlements are therefore a superior way to diversify a portfolio and to secure an investment that will not fluctuate with random and unexpected political, natural and social WHO CAN INVEST? This offering is open to accredited and qualified HOW MUCH SHOULD I INVEST? The minimum investment on the LiST platform is $10,000 in most When looking at assets, it is important to diversify your If you aim to diversify, it is wise to invest a small amount in a single policy rather than committing the total amount you plan to invest in the asset Have any questions? Investing in assets or loans is not risk The main unknown in LiST investments is the longevity of the policy There are several other risks to consider including, but not limited to: carrier risk, policy risks and lapsing of policy At LiST, we do our best to perform due diligence on every However, some of these risks are unpredictable and can have a dramatic impact on We advise you not to invest any amount that you can’t afford to lose in WHY IS THE POLICYHOLDER RAISING FUNDS THROUGH LiST TO FUND THE PREMIUMS? Policies are sold in the secondary market for several One of the main reasons for someone to sell their policy is that the cost of maintaining the policy tends to increase to high and unaffordable premium In many cases, the insured has had the policy for several decades and sometimes ends up not paying the premiums, resulting in the policy Others sell the entire policy to investors for a small amount and don’t benefit from the proceeds upon LiST provides policyholders with an solution where they can stop paying premiums and still benefit from the proceeds upon Sellers also appreciate LiST’s transparency throughout the HOW CAN I KEEP INFORMED ABOUT THE STATUS OF MY INVESTMENT? The project was incubated at X, Alphabet’s Moonshot Factory , which applies audacious thinking and radical new technologies to solve the world’s most challenging Based on the research they’d seen, X identified the Malta system as a product that had the potential to unlock a wealth of inexpensive clean energy to address global energy X’s team designed individual system components and evaluated whether the concept could work in the real world at a competitive The next two years were spent incubating the concept with a focus on derisking the most challenging concepts When it became clear that the technology had potential to be commercially viable at grid scale, Malta was formed outside of Alphabet as its own independent On a Mission to Build the Future of Energy Storage Systems Based in Cambridge, Massachusetts, the Malta team demonstrates proven leadership in energy strategies and robust engineering talent in power generation Malta has buttressed this core team with the formation of a syndicate of investors and energy industry partners to build and operate its first pilot of an energy storage Team Ramya Swaminathan Chief Executive Officer Ramya Swaminathan led the of Malta from X, Alphabet s Moonshot Factory (formerly Google X). She joined Malta from Rye Development, where she was CEO, , and Member of the Board of FFP New Under her leadership, Rye Development grew to be the leading developer of new hydropower projects in the United States and its portfolio of development projects, held at its holdco affiliate, FFP New Hydro, advanced from concept through FERC licensing and late stage development She was also responsible for the expansion of Rye’s platform into energy storage, with the addition of two sizable pumped hydro storage development projects in the Pacific At Rye Development, Swaminathan led a team, with specialists in engineering and construction, regulatory and environmental aspects, and power She also led the company through several financing rounds, both at the platform and the project Prior to her work in the hydropower space, Swaminathan was a public finance banker, most recently as a Director at UBS, where she focused on public power clients and senior managed more than $10 billion in Swaminathan holds a Master’s in Public Policy from the John Kennedy School of Government and a BA in Anthropology from Amherst Benjamin Bollinger, VP of Engineering Ben Bollinger joined Malta with a background in energy storage and From to , Ben was Chief Engineer and at SustainX, where he led the systems engineering and process design of the company’s Isothermal Compressed Air Energy Storage (ICAES) Through three development iterations - kW to commercial prototype - and nearly $40 million raised over 8 years, Ben has seen many of the ups, downs, and pitfalls that startups can run In the interim three years, Ben was VP of Engineering at Altaeros, a startup developing large autonomous aerostats (tethered balloons) to enable the deployment of rural telecommunications Ben received his PhD and BE from the Thayer School of Engineering focusing on acoustics, medical imaging, and signal processing, and his BA from Dartmouth College focusing on mechanical engineering and Elvir Mujanovic VP Finance Elvir Mujanovic joined Malta from Rye Development, where he was VP of At Rye Development, Elvir was responsible for overseeing corporate finance, accounting, and project financing Prior to FFP, Elvir spent four years at UBS and Merrill Lynch structuring more than $3 billion of assets backed bonds for state housing f

FAQ — Street FC 0 Skip to Content Rules FAQ Shop Open Menu Close Menu Rules FAQ Shop Open Menu Close Menu Rules FAQ Shop What is Street FC? Street FC is building the biggest football club on the We host street soccer games on surfaces in cities around the USA, and we’re assembling a giant community full of players and Our game format is designed to make soccer accessible to as many people as possible – providing a level playing field for men and women, girls and boys, and people of all ages and skill The Street FC app is core to the experience and it allows players to book into games, helps to manage players of different skill levels, and works to connect our community of players online and in the real What are Street FC games like? Street FC games are street soccer games played on hard Players book into minute “sessions” and we play as many 4 minute “games” as we can in each 1 hour Each session has players, each game is (three teams total), with a “winner stays” format deciding who gets to play We keep score, but not And, we are constantly switching up the teams to keep the play You can learn more from reading our rules . Is Street FC in my city? We aspire to bring Street FC to cities around the US and around the We’re currently live in NYC NJ, Boston, Philly, Baltimore, Atlanta, Minneapolis, Austin, Denver, Las Vegas, Los Angeles and San If you would like to bring Street FC to your city, please let us Before we launch in a city, we do try to find an amazing place where we can play , so if you’ve seen great courts or in your neighborhood, let us Why only hard surfaces and games? We are focused on making soccer as accessible as possible to as many people as That means playing on spaces in cities (where concrete is easy to find, while grass and turf are not) and leveling the playing field to make speed and strength less important to be Small sided games on hard surfaces accomplish What skill level do I have to be to play? Depending on the city you’re in, you can be of any skill level to enjoy playing in a Street FC In some cities, we currently host games for Beginners, Intermediate, and Advanced We also aspire to offer games for people who have never played before and for youth players of all levels and If your skill level doesn’t match any of the games we are offering, please let us know . How do I get into a game? Download the Street FC app to get Our weekly game schedule drops on Sunday night, and we allow players to book games up to 8 days in Our games fill up fast, so make sure to have the Street FC app handy when new games are about to If you miss out, you can always join a game’s “waitlist” (and as a waitlist grows, we often spawn new games and send a notification to those who may want to join). What should I bring to a game? We bring all the gear (goals, balls, pinnies), so all you need to do is bring clothes to play in and some shoes (no cleats, no spikes). Bring some water and a good attitude too! What happens if I can’t make it? If you can’t make it, no We just ask that you give our community enough time to fill your spot (our games are most fun when all spots are filled!). You can read more about our cancelation policy here [insert link]. How much does Street FC cost? When you join Street FC, your first game is After that, players choose to become Street FC Members ($35 month) to play in unlimited games or purchase “Guest Passes” for $10 game. When you become a Street FC member, you receive full access to the Street FC community including our Discord chat server , merch drops, invites to events and watch parties, and other exclusive perks and Free Guess Passes are also available to players who refer their friends to download our app and and play in Street FC How do I get a refund? If your game is canceled because of weather or other unforeseen circumstances, you will automatically be refunded your Guest In the event you’d like a refund for other reasons, please contact us . How old do I have to be to play? Our games are currently meant for adults (18+) although we often make exceptions to skilled players (15 and up). You can reach out to us directly if you’re over and would like to play in a match (as we may need written consent from your parent or guardian). How can I get involved? How can I host games? We’re always looking for “Game Captains” to help us host more Street FC games and bring Street FC to more We pay our Game Captains a for hosting games (a gig that includes greeting players, recruiting players, bringing gear to games, and set up and clean up). If you’d like to learn more, please reach out . What does a Street FC court look like? The ideal court is about the size of a basketball court (100 feet long x feet wide) with a that is not slick (concrete and asphalt are great, sealed concrete and SportCourt™ surfaces are less great). The court itself should have good ball retention (with a fence or wall surrounding it), and be in a safe and area with good Don’t worry if the space doesn’t

Natural Gas Liquids Pipeline Systems from Williams December 6, | In News | By eastonenergy HOUSTON , 6, PRNewswire — Easton Energy LLC (“Easton” or the “Company”), a Houston based midstream company, today announced the acquisition of approximately miles of Gulf Coast natural gas liquids (NGL) pipelines from The Williams Companies, (NYSE: WMB) for $177 million in The pipeline assets are primarily used to transport natural gas liquids from various supply sources to petrochemical consumers in Texas and Louisiana The transaction was completed in partnership with Easton’s financial sponsor, Cresta Energy Capital, an energy infrastructure focused private equity firm based in Dallas . “Paired with our salt cavern storage development at Markham, Texas , this acquisition represents an opportunity for Easton to utilize a significant footprint of pipelines to connect key NGL storage markets with end users along the Texas Gulf Coast,” said Joel McComas , President, Easton Energy . “It has been exciting to partner with Easton since its formation,” said Chris Rozzell , Managing Partner at Cresta Energy “This acquisition highlight’s Easton’s commitment to investing in much needed natural gas liquids infrastructure across the Gulf We look forward to supporting Easton’s ongoing growth as the company continues to build on its existing ” About Easton Energy LLC Easton Energy is a Houston based midstream company focused on developing infrastructure assets that support the transportation, storage, and processing of natural gas liquids (NGL), refined products, and Easton’s primary assets include liquid hydrocarbon salt cavern storage facilities at Markham, TX and approximately miles of product distribution pipelines that connect key product markets along the Texas and Louisiana Gulf Easton Energy is backed by Cresta Energy For more information, please visit: About Cresta Energy Capital Cresta Energy Capital is a Dallas based private equity firm focused on middle market infrastructure investments across the energy and related Cresta was founded in by energy infrastructure professionals that understand that executing on successful value add investment opportunities How To Get There Safely | Keyto Skip to content Keyto Premium Keyto Breath Sensor Key Eats Food Bars Snacks Essentials Key Eats Food Premium members get our delicious, Key Eats snacks at our cost to make and Bars Snacks Essentials Shop All Ketosis – What Is Ketosis? How To Get There Safely Ketosis is a metabolic state where your body burns fat instead of carbs for In many individuals being in ketosis leads to rapid and substantial Why would you want to be in ketosis? Being in ketosis and following a , ketogenic diet turns your body in to a fat burning That means you get to eat delicious foods like: cheese, charcuterie, eggs and bacon while losing weight and feeling Best of all? Many people in ketosis experience greater which means they feel fuller, faster and are less hungry You heard that right – you get to eat delicious foods while losing weight and feeling It’s a no brainer! Ketosis symptoms can include: initial rapid drop in water weight initial onset of insomnia, but improved quality of sleep in the longterm increased ketones in the blood or urine change in bowel movements reduced appetite “keto breath” – bad breath that smells of rotting fruit, baby’s breath or nail polish remover smell or color of urine may change, to be “fruity” or oily in appearance increased energy levels Generally it takes healthy individuals up to a week to achieve But good news – there’s ways you can speed up that process so you can get in to ketosis, How to achieve ketosis more quickly To get in to ketosis more quickly, follow these 5 easy tips: Stick to the keto Limiting your carb intake is crucial in order to be in While some individual are able to consume up to carbs per day, you should stick to net carbs or If you find that you are not reaching ketosis, consider counting your carbs or calculating your Try intermittent fasting or a brief fast Fasting depletes your body of carbs and calories, making it easier for you to get in to ketosis, Try exogenous ketones or MCT (coconut) oil MCT oil, also known as medium chain triglycerides (MCT’s), are naturally occurring fatty acids found in coconut or palm oils that enhance ketone production, More than % of the fatty acids in coconut oil are But start slow – it’s best to be conservative and add only tsps and work your way up to avoid a laxative Try HIIT (high intensity interval training) workouts or intense cardio The incredible caloric burn of an intense workout can help you reach a greater calorie deficit that gets you in to ketosis faster Measure your progress Be sure to measure your progress so that you can adjust your diet With the Keyto breath sensor you can measure how deep you are in ketosis with just one You can also use other solutions on the market that involve drawing blood or ketone urine strips Getting in to ketosis for vegans and vegetarians Achieving ketosis can be difficult for vegans and vegetarians, as many keto favorites like eggs or dairy are not an For those that follow a diet it’s best to rely on , sources of healthy fats like coconut oil, avocados, seeds, nuts and vegan meat replacements like tempeh and Is ketosis bad? And is it safe? If you’ve been around the interwebs, you might have heard that being in ketosis is scary or even dangerous . That couldn’t be further from the truth, because nutritional ketosis is very different from Diabetic ketoacidosis, or DKA for short, is a serious and medical condition usually associated with, you guessed To clear up the confusion, here are the key differences between ketosis ketoacidosis: Nutritional ketosis i s a natural metabolic state that was a survival mechanism during times of low food Nowadays it can be achieved by most healthy individuals through the ketogenic diet and or intermittent Blood glucose and insulin levels are usually markedly improved, even for healthy Ketoacidosis (DKA) is a rare yet potentially fatal complication of diabetes that produces a dangerously high level of ketones in the body – turning it It occurs when the body can’t create enough insulin, and can also be detected through ketone urine tests and or blood tests due to dangerously high elevation in blood sugar levels ( hypoglycemia ). But don’t just take our word for it Virta Health is a San , diabetes clinic that aims to cure diabetes through Founded in , Virta has been helping their patients get off insulin, reduce their A1c, and shed extra pounds– while reversing Their secret weapon? The keto Watch Stephen Phinney discuss the safety and benefits of a ketogenic diet, below: Our key takeaways: Study after study shows that a ketogenic diet is superior to traditional diets in affecting weight loss and adipose tissue around the abdominal This is the most dangerous fat we carry in the body In a week study calorie restricted diet experienced half the weight loss of the ketogenic diet group who was told to eat to And it wasn’t just water – water loss was only 1 5 of the weight lost in the keto diet group, the rest was

Water Harvesting Home About Us Our Team Our Technology Our Partners Contact PURE WATER FROM Anywhere About Us Water Harvesting Inc was formed in the summer of to commercialize atmospheric water harvesting systems based on MOFs (metal organic frameworks). MOFs were pioneered by Professor Omar Yaghi at the University of California, Berkeley, and have been demonstrated to work for atmospheric water harvesting application, even under very arid Water Harvesting Inc has negotiated an exclusive licensing agreement with UC Berkeley to develop and commercialize water harvesting It has also recently filed its own provisional patent application related to details of the system Water Harvesting Inc combines industry leaders, each with decades of experience, MOF experts, and a commitment to addressing the global challenge of water Our Board of Directors Laura Smoliar, PhD Chairwoman Bill Gallo Member Omar Yaghi, PhD Member Michael O Donnell Secretary Our Team Bill Gallo Chief Executive Officer Bruno Marchon, PhD Vice President of Engineering Eugene Kapustin, PhD Development Engineer Julia Jacobson Manager, Administration Taber Smith, PhD Engineering Leader Gener8 Anita Choi IP Counsel Morrison & Foerster Glass CFO EngineRoom Our Advisors Pete Johnson Director, Azimuth Capital Management Fred Kittler Founder and Managing Partner, Firelake Capital Our Technology MOFs, or frameworks, are an innovative class of materials constructed from units, joined by simple organic molecules, that result in an open crystalline MOFs are exceptionally porous: one gram of a typical MOF has a surface area which can cover an entire football Recently, MOFs have shown potential in storing hydrogen and natural gas, capturing carbon dioxide from flue gas, and for heterogeneous catalysis applications [1]. Water Harvesting Inc seeks to use MOFs as a material for water harvesting even in the most arid regions of the In , the first ever Water Harvester was built and tested by UC Berkeley, to capture water from the atmosphere [2]. In , the same team deployed a MOF harvester powered by natural sunlight in Arizona, to produce water of drinking quality [3-4]. Professor Omar Yaghi s new, patented , is based on aluminum cations linked by 3 acid It is synthesized in water, does not require any catalyst, and can be to industrial One unique feature of this MOF is that it works like a sponge to atmospheric It captures water even under extremely low humidity and high temperature conditions, and unlike other porous materials such as zeolites, water does not require much heat to desorb from MOF materials, making them the materials of choice for water harvesting in dry Water Harvesting Inc now owns the exclusive rights to commercialize the use of UC Berkeley s MOF materials for atmospheric water For this purpose, we have developed a technology that exploits the unique ability of MOF materials to adsorb and release water seamlessly, with little energy penalty, unlike conventional, water We have filed a provisional Patent Application (#62 795,332) describing the system design, and plan on offering commercial units for purchase in the near [1] The Chemistry and Applications of Frameworks, Science (2013) [2] Water Harvesting from Air with Frameworks Powered by Natural Sunlight, Science (2017) [3] Atmospheric Water Harvesting Device for Arid Climates, Nature Communications (2018) [4] Practical Water Production from Desert Air, Science Advances (2018) Our Partners Contact Us Send us an email (click below) and we will get back to you as soon as possible!
